Russian Reserves Slide to $510.4 Billion, Lowest Since April

-- B y   S c o t t   R o s e
-- 
2011-10-13T10:41:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/russian-reserves-slide-to-510-4-billion-lowest-since-april.html
Russia’s international gold and
currency reserves dropped $6.4 billion to $510.4 billion in the
week ending Oct. 7, the lowest level since April, according to
the central bank’s website. The reserves have fallen for the
past five weeks, the longest stretch of declines since November
2008, Bank Rossii said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
